Angola, Africa's third-largest economy, has just signed a deal with GE to supply seven TM2500 gas turbine sets capable of generating electricity to meet the needs of 15 percent of Angola's population. Mark Egan writes in GE Reports how each TM2500 gas turbine is actually an "aeroderivative" derived from the same technology found in GE airplane jet engines. Read more. More about GE in Africa in this BRIEFING.&nbsp;&nbsp;